## <a id="credhub"></a> CredHub Documentation

CredHub provides centralized credential management in Ops Manager. Credentials can include passwords, certificates, and SSH keys.

CredHub centralizes and secures credential generation, storage, lifecycle management, and system access.

These topics provide general information about CredHub:

* [CredHub](https://docs.pivotal.io/credhub/index.html)
* [CredHub Credential Types](https://docs.pivotal.io/credhub/credential-types.html)


## <a id="uaa"></a> UAA Documentation

Ops Manager uses User Account and Authentication (UAA) to manage account roles and permissions in Ops Manager runtimes.

UAA supports access control as OAuth2 services and can store user information internally, or connect to external user stores through LDAP or SAML.

These topics provide general information about UAA:

* [UAA Overview](https://docs.pivotal.io/application-service/uaa/uaa-overview.html)
* [UAA Concepts](https://docs.pivotal.io/application-service/uaa/uaa-concepts.html)
* [UAA Architecture](https://docs.pivotal.io/application-service/2-7/concepts/architecture/uaa.html)
* [Identity Providers in UAA](https://docs.pivotal.io/application-service/uaa/identity-providers.html)


